name: EB-001-Bowie
description:
David Bowie, stage name of David Robert Jones, (London, January 8, 1947—New York, January 10, 2016) was a British singer, songwriter, actor and record producer. Sometimes referred to as the "Rock Chameleon" for his ability to always renew his image, he has been an important figure in popular music for five decades and is considered one of the most innovative and still influential folk musicians of all time, particularly for his work in the 1970s and 1980s, as well as being distinguished by a characteristic vocal and the intellectual depth of his work.

Digital Watercolor Vector Illustration made in Adobe Photoshop, 1200x1200px, 200dpi, JPEG, 2021
